  "script": "2 million bees loose? In Texas, a semi truck hauling beehives flipped on a highway and unleashed an estimated two million honeybees into the open air at once. Police did the only sane thing and told everyone nearby to stay indoors, windows shut, while the air itself turned into a living, buzzing cloud. Beekeepers in full suits rushed in to corral the swarm before it scattered for good. One wrong move near two million stressed-out bees is a trip to the hospital. Picture a traffic jam where the hazard isn't cars — it's a stinging fog you can't drive through. So what do you even do when the road is full of two million angry bees?",
